<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/2093830-karenc">KarenC</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    **** SPOILER ALERT !! **** If you haven't finished don't read this response. <br />&lt;spoiler&gt;You have to be reading carefully to catch it. Basically had Audi<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    **** SPOILER ALERT !! **** If you haven't finished don't read this response. <br />&lt;spoiler&gt;You have to be reading carefully to catch it. Basically had Audie not escaped he would have been killed by Sheriff Valdez on the day of his release. Valdez went to the prison to meet him at the gate. Valdez &amp; his co-conspirators hired people to kill Audie while he as in prison, but the attempts were unsuccessful, mostly thanks to Moss. I nearly missed it myself, but after leafing back through and giving it some thought the reason became clear. &lt;/spoiler&gt;<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
