  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1119722185" />
    <a title="Frances" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/37439004-frances"><img alt="Frances" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1419968891p2/37439004.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1119722185?book_show_action=true">Nov 30, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Frances" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Frances" href="/user/show/37439004-frances">Frances</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780751552904" href="/book/show/20569350-life-or-death">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/37439004-frances?shelf=favourite-books">favourite-books</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1119722185" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7957632050521434381">An Extraordinary Book!<br/>I recently discovered this author and after reading ‘Bombproof’ I wrote that it was “one” of the best books read this year. Having just completed ‘Life or Death’, it is definitely “the best” book I’ve read this year (maybe even last year as well). The story is about Audie Palmer who was about to become a free man after finishing a ten year sentence in prison. So the question is, why would he escape the day before his release? Now on the run this book soon becomes a page tur</span>
  <span id="freeText7957632050521434381" style="display:none">An Extraordinary Book!<br />I recently discovered this author and after reading ‘Bombproof’ I wrote that it was “one” of the best books read this year. Having just completed ‘Life or Death’, it is definitely “the best” book I’ve read this year (maybe even last year as well). The story is about Audie Palmer who was about to become a free man after finishing a ten year sentence in prison. So the question is, why would he escape the day before his release? Now on the run this book soon becomes a page turner and one of those hard to put down novels. It has remarkable characters throughout, along with his usual flare for snazzy, intelligent writing. If you haven’t read a Michael Robotham before you are in for a real treat with this extraordinary book.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="7957632050521434381" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


